a |year=2011 |publisher=CaribeInsider.com |accessdate=25 June 2011 <!--|quote=El ave nacional de Anguila es el Turtle Dove (Zenaida Aurita).-->}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |{{ATG}} || [[Fallow deer]] ''(national animal)''||''Dama dama'' || [[File:Fallow deer in field.jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=\"aggov\">{{cite web|url=http://ab.gov.ag/gov_v4/article_details.php?id=179&category=66|title=Official Website for the Government of Antigua and Barbuda|publisher=ab.gov.ag|accessdate=2011-08-19|author=Government of Antigua and Barbuda}}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Magnificent frigatebird|Frigate]] ''(national bird)''||''Fregata magnificens'' || [[File:Fregata magnificens1.jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=\"aggov\" />\n|-\n|[[Hawksbill sea turtle|Hawksbill turtle]] ''(national sea creature)''||''Eretmochelys imbricata'' || [[File:Hawksbill Turtle.jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=\"aggov\" />\n|-\n|{{ARG}} || [[Rufous hornero]] ||''Furnarius rufus'' || [[File:Flickr - Dario Sanches - JO\u00c3O-DE-BARRO (Furnarius rufus) (3).jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.redargentina.com/Faunayflora/Aves/hornero.asp |title=Info about Hornero |language=Spanish |publisher=Redargentina.com |date=24 September 2007 |accessdate=25 April 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113022038/http://www.redargentina.com/Faunayflora/Aves/hornero.asp |archivedate=13 November 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{AUS}} || [[Red kangaroo]] ''(national animal)''||''Macropus rufus'' ||[[File:Red kangaroo - melbourne zoo.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Gregory |first1=Herbert E. |year=1916 |title=Lonely Australia: The Unique Continent |journal=National Geographic |volume=XXX |issue=6 |page=497 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rgcVAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA497#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=19 June 2011 }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Emu]] ''(national bird)''||''Dromaius novaehollandiae'' || [[File:Emoe.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http:/