stine adopts sunbird as emblem for exported goods|last=Qais|first=Abu Samra|date=September 18, 2018|work=[[Anadolu Agency]]|access-date=October 4, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{PAN}} || [[Harpy eagle]] ||''Harpia harpyja'' ||[[File:Harpia harpyja 001 800.jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=\"6 Extremely Rare National Animals\"/>\n|-\n|{{PNG}} || [[Dugong]] ''(national marine mammal)'' ||''Dugong dugon'' ||[[File:Dugong Marsa Alam.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Hudson |first1=Brydget E.T. |year=1981 |title=Interview and Aerial Survey Data in Relation to Resource Management of the Dugong in Manus Province, Papua New Guinea  |journal=Bulletin of Marine Science |volume=31 |issue=3 |pages=662\u2013672 |url=http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/umrsmas/bullmar/1981/00000031/00000003/art00018 |accessdate=4 July 2011 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{PER}} || [[Vicu\u00f1a]] ''(national animal)'' ||''Vicugna vicugna'' ||[[File:Vicunacrop.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/ten-unusual-national-animals-rival-unicorn-180952804/?no-ist |title=Ten Unusual National Animals That Rival the Unicorn-9 of 10 |publisher=smithsonianmag.com |accessdate=2014-10-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{PHL}}\n|[[Philippine eagle]] ''(national bird)''||''Pithecophaga jefferyi''||[[File:Sir Arny(Philippine Eagle).jpg|150px]]||<ref name=\"phsymeagle\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gov.ph/1995/07/04/proclamation-no-615-s-1995/ |title=Proclamation No. 615, s. 1995 |publisher=gov.ph|accessdate=2012-08-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |{{POL}} || [[White-tailed eagle]] ''(national bird)''||''Haliaeetus albicilla'' || [[File:White-tailed Eagle Head detail.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://birds.poland.pl/directory/gallery%2CWhite-tailed_Eagle_%28Haliaeetus_albicilla%29%2Cgid%2C236008%2Ccid%2C923.htm |title=Polish Birds Directory: White-tailed Eagle (Haliaeetus albicilla) |publisher=birds.poland.pl |accessdate=2016-10-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080616044037/http://bir