|Lists}}\n* [[State animal]]\n* [[List of national birds]]\n* [[Animals as heraldic charges]]\n* [[Floral emblem]]\n* [[National personification]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{-}}\n{{National symbols}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of National Animals}}\n[[Category:Lists of national symbols|Animal]]\n[[Category:Lists of animals]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n<!-- WARNING: Adding an animal to this list *requires* a reliable source. Uncited additions will be removed -->\n\nThis is a '''list of national animals'''.\n\n==National animals==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!align=left|Country\n!align=left|Name of animal\n!align=left|Scientific name  ([[Latin]] name)\n!align=left|Pictures\n!align=left|[[Reference|Ref.]]\n|-\n|{{AFG}} || [[Snow leopard]] ||''Panthera uncia'' || [[File:Snow leopard in Afghanistan.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/asia/afghanistan/afsymbols.htm|title=Afghani Symbols|publisher=worldatlas.com|accessdate=2019-03-09}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{ALB}} || [[Eagle]] || ''Accipitridae''|| [[File:Aquila chrysaetos La Canada 2012-01-14.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite book|last=Elsie|first=Robert|author-link=Robert Elsie|title=A Dictionary of Albanian Religion, Mythology and Folk Culture|place=London|publisher=Hurst & Company|url=https://books.google.com/?id=N_IXHrXIsYkC&dq|isbn=1-85065-570-7|year=2001|p=78}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{ALG}} || [[Fennec fox]] ||''Vulpes zerda'' || [[File:Fennec Foxes.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.algeria.com/blog/the-fennec-fox-algeria-s-national-animal|title=The Fennec Fox: Algeria's National Animal|publisher=algeria.com|accessdate=2013-03-21}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{AGO}} || [[Red-crested turaco]] ''(national bird)'' ||''Tauraco erythrolophus'' || [[File:RedcrestedTuraco.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.birdsangola.org/nationalbird.htm |title=THE NATIONAL BIRD OF ANGOLA|website=BIRDS ANGOLA |accessdate=12 Apr